"""Async core client for AgentPulse.

``AsyncAgentPulseClient`` runs a connection loop against ``/ws/v2``,
runs bootstrap REST fetches on connect/reconnect, applies frames to a
``ClientStore``, and exposes snapshot accessors plus callback hooks. On
disconnect the store is **not** cleared — last-known data is preserved
and the connection state advertises staleness.

Bootstrap is two REST calls:

1. ``GET /api/v2/sessions?since=<midnight>`` — every session touched
   today, active or ended.
2. ``GET /api/v2/log/statuslines?since=<midnight>&order=desc&limit=1000``
   — seeds tokens / lines / cost for those sessions
   (``SessionResponse`` doesn't carry these). Limit is the endpoint cap;
   busy days will leave less-active sessions at zero until their next
   live frame.

When ``config.fetch_limits`` is True a third call seeds the latest
``api_limits`` row.
"""

